------------------------------------------------Day 1 of HTML(September 19, 2025)------------------------------------------------------


HTML - HyperText Markup Language.


HTML is the foundational building block of the web. 

It provides the skeleton or structural layer of a webpage, defining its content and basic layout.

While you can write HTML code in a simple text file (and save it with a .html extension), the best practice is to use a dedicated code editor like Visual Studio Code (VS Code).

Editors like VS Code provide essential features such as syntax highlighting, auto-completion, and error detection, which make writing code faster and less error-prone.






Assignments :-

Install VSCode and send me the screenshot.

Explore some extensions in VSCode to look code beautifully.

